This paper deals with the integrity and preservation of data in digital repositories, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a treap-based persistent authenticated dictionary, which is a data structure commonly used in computer science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the distributed nature of the system, which could fall under the categories of distributed systems (cs.DC) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper describes the implementation and performance of the system, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
